Most stunning beauty: Michelle Pfeiffer Worst reader of Teleprompter: Walter Matthau. Most welcomed elimination: Singing of the nominees for best song. Warmest reception: Lucille Ball and Bob Hope. The most intelligent acceptance: Jodie Foster.  handed out the first awards in 1929 in five minutes. The brightest moments of the 61st Awards came from Billy Crystal, Robin Williams and Bob Hope, but they were all too brief. The use of couples, co-stars, compadres and companions, as presenters for the 61st Academy Awards at the Shrine Auditorium was clever but wearing. Too many endless production numbers. 